The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Mumbai, June 19: An army major working at a recruitment office in Mumbai was today arrested by the CBI while accepting a bribe of Rs 50,000 from a jawan.           
	Major Dipendra Bhushan, posted as a medical officer at the recruitment office, had taken Rs 10,000 from the jawan earlier in the evening for issuing a certificate clearing his medical examination. The CBI said the major had confessed to taking bribe.                  
	 Washington (PTI): A software engineer from Andhra Pradesh was robbed and shot dead by a group of five persons in a motel near Detroit, where he had gone to meet a Mexican woman. Police have arrested the five persons involved in the murder of Venkata Subba Reddy Cuttamanchi, 35, on Wednesday. Those arrested include the boyfriend of the woman.                   
	 Chennai: Single Hindu women and widows will be allowed to adopt children if Parliament passes a bill that calls for amendments to Hindu laws. The parliamentary standing committee to which the bill has been referred has received near unanimity that the restrictions on Hindu women adopting children should be removed, Jayanthi Natarajan, the chairman of the parliamentary panel on personnel, public grievances, law and justice, said.                   
	Mumbai (PTI): The decomposed body of an eight-year-old girl, suspected to have been killed after rape, has been found in a dilapidated building in Kurla, police said.                                                                                                                                              
